ðŸ”¹ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. Which function returns total of a numeric column?
A. COUNT
B. AVG
C. SUM
D. TOTAL

2. Which function counts number of rows?
A. SUM()
B. COUNT()
C. AVG()
D. TOTAL()

3. What does AVG() return?
A. Total rows
B. Sum of values
C. Average value
D. Maximum value

4. Which clause groups rows with same values?
A. ORDER BY
B. GROUP BY
C. HAVING
D. WHERE

5. Which clause filters grouped data?
A. WHERE
B. GROUP BY
C. HAVING
D. ORDER BY

6. Which query counts all employees?
A. SELECT COUNT(emp) FROM emp;
B. SELECT COUNT() FROM emp;
C. SELECT TOTAL() FROM emp;
D. SELECT SUM(*) FROM emp;

7. Aggregate functions operate on:
A. Single row
B. Multiple rows
C. Only integers
D. Only strings

8. Which clause must appear after GROUP BY?
A. WHERE
B. HAVING
C. SELECT
D. FROM

9. What is a subquery?
A. Query inside JOIN
B. Query inside another query
C. Query with GROUP BY
D. Query with ORDER BY

10. Which keyword is used to compare with subquery result?
A. WITH
B. IN
C. BETWEEN
D. JOIN

ðŸ”¸ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
11. Which query calculates average salary?
A. SELECT salary FROM emp;
B. SELECT AVG(salary) FROM emp;
C. SELECT salary/COUNT() FROM emp;
D. SELECT AVG() FROM emp;

12. Difference between WHERE and HAVING?
A. Same
B. WHERE filters rows, HAVING filters groups
C. HAVING faster
D. WHERE used with aggregates

13. Which is valid GROUP BY query?
A. SELECT dept, SUM(salary) FROM emp;
B. SELECT dept, SUM(salary) FROM emp GROUP BY dept;
C. SELECT SUM(salary) FROM emp GROUP dept;
D. SELECT dept FROM emp SUM(salary);

14. Which clause is evaluated first?
A. HAVING
B. GROUP BY
C. WHERE
D. SELECT

15. Which query finds departments with more than 5 employees?
A.

SELECT dept FROM emp WHERE COUNT(*) > 5;
B.

SELECT dept FROM emp GROUP BY dept HAVING COUNT(*) > 5;
C.

SELECT dept HAVING COUNT(*) > 5 FROM emp;
D.

SELECT dept WHERE COUNT(*) > 5 FROM emp;
16. Which function ignores NULL values?
A. SUM
B. AVG
C. COUNT(column)
D. All of the above

17. Which subquery returns multiple values?
A. Scalar subquery
B. Correlated subquery
C. Multi-row subquery
D. Nested join

18. Which operator is used with multi-row subquery?
A. =
B. >
C. IN
D. !=

19. Which subquery depends on outer query?
A. Nested
B. Scalar
C. Correlated
D. Independent

20. Subqueries can appear in:
A. SELECT
B. WHERE
C. FROM
D. All of the above

