22. Which query is INVALID?
A. SELECT dept, COUNT() FROM emp GROUP BY dept;
B. SELECT dept, salary FROM emp GROUP BY dept;
C. SELECT dept FROM emp GROUP BY dept HAVING COUNT()>1;
D. SELECT dept, AVG(salary) FROM emp GROUP BY dept;

23. Why WHERE cannot use aggregate functions?
A. Syntax limitation
B. WHERE executes before aggregation
C. WHERE slower
D. WHERE ignores groups

24. Which HAVING condition is valid?
A. HAVING salary > 50000
B. HAVING AVG(salary) > 50000
C. WHERE AVG(salary) > 50000
D. WHERE COUNT(*) > 5

25. Which subquery executes once per row?
A. Scalar
B. Multi-row
C. Correlated
D. Inline

26. Which clause improves performance when filtering rows before grouping?
A. HAVING
B. WHERE
C. ORDER BY
D. SELECT

27. COUNT() vs COUNT(column):
A. Both same
B. COUNT(column) counts NULLs
C. COUNT() includes NULL rows
D. COUNT(*) counts rows, COUNT(column) ignores NULLs

28. Which returns single value?
A. Multi-row subquery
B. Correlated subquery
C. Scalar subquery
D. Inline view

29. Which is CCEE-common trap?
A. AVG syntax
B. GROUP BY missing column
C. SUM on strings
D. HAVING before GROUP BY

30. Best practice for complex filtering is:
A. Nested subqueries
B. WHERE + HAVING combo
C. Filtering early with WHERE
D. Avoid GROUP BY

